<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101225231232899></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101225231232899><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=quest.html?quest=454&mid=101225231232899>Time of PH Kill does NOT trigger Grimrot</a> <a id=fs8 href=quest.html?quest=454&mid=101225231232899#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=76269><span id=Scholar>YtrillStonebow</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>16 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jan 28th 5:13 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have been doing this quest for my cleric, and the information in this forum has been very helpful.<br><br>Just to clarify what seems to be a misconception in some threads: killing the PH at a certain time does NOT trigger a spawn of Grimrot. Whenever the PH is killed, irrespective of the EQ time, the next spawn is either another PH or Grimrot.<br><br>The only reason to kill the PH at a specific time is to have a chance that the Grimrot YOU NEED will spawn. If the respawn is during the day, it will be the PH or live Grimrot; if at night, the PH or dead Grimrot. Hence, if you have the heart from the dead Grimrot already, you want to time the killing of each PH so that the next spawn will be in the daytime. That way, you have a chance to get the live version.<br><br>If you need both quest items, you're wasting time by not killing the PH as soon as it spawns. I found the PH uncamped, killed it at 11 PM game time, and got the live Grimrot on the next spawn.<br><br>Hope this helps, and good luck to all!<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
