	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>It took 3 weeks for me to get Grimrot. Yep 3 weeks of camping him on and off. Got 5 live ones before I got the undead version. Tried everyone's theories about times etc and what worked for me in the end was this: kill the placeholder between 6am and 9am to spawn the undead one. Kill the PH between 6pm and 9pm to get the live one. The PH will spawn on time, when Grimrot spawns, it was always a bit late.<br><br>At 50, undead grimmy is so green - live Grimrot is light blue - had a paladin do the killing for me anyway and the pally managed to bash and interrupt that harm touch. Interesting to know, 'cos harmtouch is a skill not a spell. Another time a lion ran thru just as live Grimmy spawned and Mr Lion got the harmtouch instead LOL. As for faction, well I stopped bothering to kill the putrids after the first week, but killing 5 Grimrots made me Ally. I still fed 400 gold coins &quot;just to be sure&quot; even though I knew my faction must've been high enough (I wasn't going thru all that again). The corrupt guards have become threatening, most are green tho at my level and are no problem except for Dagarok who's also 50.<br><br>Oh yeah, watch out for stupid aviaks attacking the skels. I've lost the PH to those birds. The dwarf skelly others mention is for a Kaladim quest and is unrelated to Grimrot or Granex the undead gnoll needed for monks. Grahnex spawns near a tree on the edge of the camp. Also, sometimes live Grimrot will spawn in the middle of the night, just to mess with you. Very glad that's over and good luck to anyone else attempting it.<br><br>Panadoll<br>50 Cleric, Bristlebane.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
